<br>
I WAS following this track until they (read: Education Department) decided to spring some extra requirements on me.  I had carefully planned my Gen Ed classes and made sure I filled all the requirements for the college (math, science, etc.).  English is considered a Humanity/Liberal Art, SO I was not required to have &quot;hard math or science&quot; requirements to fill.  Naturally I chose Probability and Statistics and Contemporary College Math for my Math requirements.  I took Astronomy for my Science.  I enjoyed them, got my As (B for Stats) and moved on.<br>
<br>
The Ed department suddenly decided that they wanted me to take another Math and another Lab science!  They also wanted them to be &quot;Hard&quot;.  So next thing you know, they are trying to schedule me for Calc, and Chemistry!!!  I was like &quot;HOLD THE PHONE!  There is a REASON I am an English Major... because I SUCK at Math and Science!!!&quot;  So I dropped Secondary Education as a Minor with a few colorful phrases on what they can do with their department, and walked out.  You can do a lot more with an English Degree anyway besides teach.  Maybe I will try my hand at Editing, Writing, or even attempt Law School for a bit... who knows... but teaching is now officially out. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skedaddle@firionavie>Skedaddle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/20/03 11:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3898.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I fear for my childs education...</span><hr size=1> On Long Island, NY, there is a small commuter college called Dowling College.  <br>
<br>
When I lived in NY a couple of years ago, they were running a major ad campaign, which involved plastering the backs and sides of commercial buses with the following slogan:<br>
<br>
&quot;Why Not Dowling.&quot;<br>
<br>
Every time I saw that advertisement, I had  the response: &quot;because I want my children to learn proper use of punctuation.&quot; <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mediaservice.photoisland.com/auction/May/2003517426396415772"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END-->[/image]</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=artanisbor>Artanis Bor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Champion of Sarcasm</span><br>  Posts: 128<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/20/03 2:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3898.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.wideopenwest.com/~rsinatra/images/ayb01.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I fear for my childs education...</span><hr size=1> hukt on fonix werkt fer me! <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=213174" target="new"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.wideopenwest.com/~rsinatra/images/art-sig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
